    <note>Ma(2) Youzhi [20694] He was the only member of his lineage to abandon farming for classicist occupations. He entered the imperial university was was granted a nominal position in 1099 and then accompanied Li(2) Zhai [14299] on his travels. Zhai considered him to be wise and worthy and arranged for Youzhi's marriage with the daughter of Zhai's elder brother. YLDD, 2368.5b. CBD, 3, 1834-5.</note>
